    "Description": "📍 About the Event\n\nThe Code Storm event is organized at\nMarwadi University\nas part of their annual tech-cultural fest called eMUlate (MUFest).\n\n📅 It is usually held during the fest (for example: 4–6 February 2026).\n\n💻 What is “Code Storm”?\n\nCode Storm is a technical coding competition where students:\n\nSolve programming problems\n\nCompete with other participants\n\nTest their logic, speed, and coding skills\n\nWork under time pressure\n\nIt is similar to:\n\nCompetitive programming contest\n\nHackathon-style mini coding challenge\n\n⚙️ Main Features\n\n⏱️ Time-based challenge (limited time to solve problems)\n\n🧠 Logic & algorithm-based questions\n\n💻 Can include languages like C, C++, Java, Python\n\n🏆 Winners are selected based on:\n\nCorrect solutions\n\nSpeed of submission\n\n🎯 Purpose of Code Storm\n\nImprove coding & problem-solving skills\n\nEncourage competitive programming\n\nPrepare students for placements & coding interviews\n\nPromote technical learning beyond classroom",
